Documents concern St. Louis Circuit Attorney Kimberly Gardner's alleged misconduct in botched prosecution of ex-Missouri governor

The Missouri Court of Appeals, Eastern District, ruled Tuesday that St. Louis' top prosecutor must hand over records concerning her bungled prosecution of former Gov. Eric Greitens to Just the News CEO and Editor in Chief John Solomon, who filed an open-records request for the documents.

AMSTERDAM (Reuters) ‚Äì     Signify NV, the world‚Äôs largest lighting maker, reported a 6% increase in fourth-quarter core earnings on Friday, as higher sales offset a rapid increase in the prices of raw materials and components. -  Adjusted earnings before interest, taxes and amortisation (EBITA) came in at 265 million euros ($295.6 million) in the last three months of 2021, as comparable sales rose 4.5% to 2 billion euros.

Signify said it expected comparable sales to grow 3% to 6% this year, with an adjusted EBITA margin of up to 12.1%, from 11.6% in 2021.

‚ÄúWhile we expect uncertainty to remain high in the first half of this year, we‚Äôre confident that we will manage this volatility‚Äù Chief Executive Officer Eric Rondolat said.
